<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hirsch</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-04-06"><hi rend="italic">April 6,
                            1892</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 308.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                        409 of 21st ultimo, and to approve your note of 14th ultimo, objecting to
                        the proposed modification of the law regulating legal matters in which
                        foreigners are concerned.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>